The culture that makes students proud of having studied all night still exists, he says, adding that modern technology and the increasing pressure on students have made sleep deprivation a growing problem.
Getting enough good-quality sleep should be a student's secret weapon against stress, exhaustion and anxiety, he said, and even to prevent weight gain, because sleep deprivation makes the brain think the body is hungry, which makes the students feel like they're constantly hungry.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old student in California studying chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler create the course after attending one of his classes in his first year at Harvard.
