We have 12 big games tomorrow and we'd like to start with some quick wins, like at Brookline, like at Medina.
When inertia develops in one direction, it puts a lot of pressure on those middle matches.
We've created the proper batch and we've ordered the players the way we want, you know, we're trying to create a little bit of magic tomorrow.
Thomas was given the task of leading the fight: he will face Rory McIlroy in the main bout, while Paul Casey, Justin Rose, Jon Rahm, Tommy Fleetwood and Ian Poulter are the other Europeans in the second half of the schedule.
