I wanted to be a member of the national football team, but as a player.
I made the national team B team and that's about it", Ross told BBC Scotland's Sportsound.
But I spent a lot of my childhood watching Scotland games at Hampden with my father and I always wanted to come back.
But I will only get this opportunity if I succeed as a manager of the club.
