The ideal time to drink a pint of beer is Saturday at 5:30, according to one poll
The heat wave this summer has led to a rise in revenues in pubs across the UK, but put more pressure on restaurant chains.
According to the figures, pubs and bars increased by 2,7% in July, while restaurant revenues decreased by 4,8%.
Peter Martin, representative of business consultancy CGA who conducted the survey, said: The constant heat and England's longer than expected World Cup attendance contributed to a pattern in July similar to the previous month, with pubs registering up to 2.8% more customers while restaurants had a worse period.
